Smart Wi-Fi Dimmer Switches.definition: Dimmer switches with built-in Wi-Fi connectivity for remote control and smart home integration, e.g. wireless app-controlled dimmers, voice assistant compatible dimmers, WiFi-enabled brightness controls

Smart Hub-Based Dimmer Switches.definition: Dimmer switches that require a separate hub or bridge for smart functionality and connectivity, e.g. hub-dependent smart dimmers, bridge-connected lighting controls

Toggle Slide Dimmer Switches.definition: Traditional dimmer switches with toggle on/off and sliding dimmer control mechanisms, e.g. slide-control dimmers, toggle-slide combination switches, linear slide controls with toggle

Touch Control Dimmer Switches.definition: Dimmer switches operated by touch-sensitive controls rather than mechanical switches, e.g. touch-activated dimmers, capacitive touch light controls, tap dimmers

Digital Display Dimmer Switches.definition: Dimmer switches featuring digital displays or electronic interfaces for precise control, e.g. LCD dimmer controls, digital readout light switches

Rotary Dimmer Switches.definition: Dimmer switches controlled by rotating knobs or dials for brightness adjustment, e.g. dial-controlled dimmers, rotary brightness controls

Standard Wall-Mount Dimmer Switches.definition: Traditional wall-mounted dimmer switches designed for basic lighting control without specialized mechanisms, e.g. wall-plate dimmers, conventional brightness controls, basic light dimmers

Dual Function Dimmer Switches.definition: Dimmer switches that control both lighting and fan functions in a single unit, e.g. fan-light combination controls, dual-purpose dimmer switches

Low Voltage Dimmer Switches.definition: Specialized dimmer switches for low voltage lighting systems and commercial applications, e.g. 0-10V dimmers, commercial LED panel controls

Wireless Companion Dimmer Switches.definition: Wireless remote controls and companion devices for multi-location dimmer control, e.g. wireless remotes, companion switch accessories, remote dimmers, auxiliary dimmers

Rocker Paddle Dimmer Switches.definition: Dimmer switches with rocker-style paddle controls for light adjustment, e.g. rocker dimmers, paddle dimmers, rocker-style brightness controls

Toggle Flip Dimmer Switches.definition: Traditional toggle-style dimmer switches with flip controls for basic on/off and dimming, e.g. toggle dimmers, flip-style dimmers, toggle brightness controls

Plug-In Portable Dimmer Switches.definition: Portable dimmer controls that plug into outlets for table lamps and portable lighting, e.g. lamp dimmers, plug-in light controls, portable brightness controls

Motion Sensor Dimmer Switches.definition: Dimmer switches with integrated motion detection for automatic lighting control, e.g. occupancy sensor dimmers, motion-activated dimmers, automatic brightness controls

Wall Mounted Slide Dimmer Switches.definition: Wall-installed dimmer switches with sliding controls for adjusting light brightness, e.g. slide control dimmers, universal slide dimmers

Wall Mounted Rotary Dimmer Switches.definition: Wall-installed dimmer switches with rotary knob controls for adjusting light brightness, e.g. rotary control dimmers, twist dial dimmers

Wall Mounted Digital Dimmer Switches.definition: Wall-installed dimmer switches with digital displays and electronic controls, e.g. digital display dimmers, electronic control dimmers

Wall Mounted Toggle Dimmer Switches.definition: Wall-installed dimmer switches with toggle-style controls for adjusting light brightness, e.g. toggle control dimmers, lever-style dimmers

Wall Mounted Rocker Dimmer Switches.definition: Wall-installed dimmer switches with rocker-style controls for adjusting light brightness, e.g. decorator rocker dimmers, paddle-style dimmers

Wall Mounted Tap Dimmer Switches.definition: Wall-installed dimmer switches with tap or touch controls for adjusting light brightness, e.g. soft tap dimmers, touch control dimmers

Advanced LED Compatible Dimmer Switches.definition: Wall-installed dimmer switches with advanced control features and LED compatibility, e.g. multi-location dimmers, advanced LED dimmers

Fluorescent Compatible Dimmer Switches.definition: Wall-installed dimmer switches designed for fluorescent and specialty lighting applications, e.g. fluorescent dimmers, specialty voltage dimmers

Smart WiFi Dimmer Switches.definition: Wall-installed dimmer switches with wireless connectivity and smart home integration, e.g. WiFi dimmers, app-controlled dimmers, voice-controlled dimmers

Smart Hub Connected Dimmer Switches.definition: Wall-installed dimmer switches that require a smart hub for connectivity and control, e.g. Z-Wave dimmers, hub-based smart dimmers

Inline Cord Dimmer Switches.definition: Portable dimmer switches that connect inline with lamp cords for table and floor lamps, e.g. cord-mounted dimmers, plug-in lamp dimmers

Dual Control Dimmer Switches.definition: Wall-installed dimmer switches that control two separate lighting circuits simultaneously, e.g. double dimmers, two-circuit dimmers
